                            <title type="incomplete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT6936TarWaAmidBeta">Tārika Walda ʾAmid (β-recension)</title>    
                            <note>The text has many similarities with <ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/BNFabb220">BNFabb220</ref> (= A) and 
                                <ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/BLorient814">BLorient814</ref> (= M). 
                                Contrary to the assumptions of <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS8249Ruppell">Eduard Rüppell</persName>, it is not a direct copy of 
                                <ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/FSUor134">FSUor134</ref>. 
                                Contrary to <bibl corresp="http://zotero.org/groups/358366/items/EFE2TAZF"><seg type="book"><!-- attributes from original bibl--></seg><ptr target="bm:Kropp2016Zekra"/><title level="m">Zekra Nagar. Die universalhistorische Einleitung nach Giyorgis Walda-Amid in der Chronikensammlung des Haylu</title><author><t:forename xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Manfred</t:forename><t:surname xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Kropp</t:surname></author><pubPlace>Speyer</pubPlace><publisher>Kartoffeldruck-Verlag Kai Brodersen</publisher><date>2016</date><citedRange unit="page">1691</citedRange></bibl>, it is 
                                not a direct copy of <ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/PetermannIINachtrag24">PetermannIINachtrag24</ref>.
                                This witness was used in 
                                <bibl corresp="http://zotero.org/groups/358366/items/GXG3M9ES"><seg type="thesis"><!-- attributes from original bibl--></seg><ptr target="bm:Hoffmann2021Amid"/><title level="m">Das geographische Traktat in der Weltgeschichte des Wäldä Amid: Text, Übersetzung und Kommentar</title><author><t:forename xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Carsten</t:forename><t:surname xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Hoffmann</t:surname></author><pubPlace>Marburg</pubPlace><date>2023</date><note type="url">https://archiv.ub.uni-marburg.de/ubfind/Record/urn:nbn:de:hebis:04-z2023-0080/View</note><citedRange unit="page">82-83</citedRange></bibl> with the 
                                Siglum H, while it was referred to as F40 in 
                                <bibl corresp="http://zotero.org/groups/358366/items/QT6D2TPP"><seg type="book"><!-- attributes from original bibl--></seg><ptr target="bm:Kropp1989Haylu"/><title level="m">Die äthiopischen Königschroniken in der Sammlung des Däǧǧazmač Ḫaylu: Entstehung und handschriftliche Überlieferung des Werks</title><title level="s">Heidelberger orientalische Studien</title><author><t:forename xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Manfred</t:forename><t:surname xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Kropp</t:surname></author><pubPlace>Frankfurt a. M.</pubPlace><publisher>Lang</publisher><date>1989</date><series><t:title xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" level="s">Heidelberger orientalische Studien</t:title><t:biblScope xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" unit="volume">13</t:biblScope></series><biblScope unit="volume">13</biblScope><citedRange unit="page">237-239</citedRange></bibl> and
                                <bibl corresp="http://zotero.org/groups/358366/items/EFE2TAZF"><seg type="book"><!-- attributes from original bibl--></seg><ptr target="bm:Kropp2016Zekra"/><title level="m">Zekra Nagar. Die universalhistorische Einleitung nach Giyorgis Walda-Amid in der Chronikensammlung des Haylu</title><author><t:forename xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Manfred</t:forename><t:surname xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Kropp</t:surname></author><pubPlace>Speyer</pubPlace><publisher>Kartoffeldruck-Verlag Kai Brodersen</publisher><date>2016</date><citedRange unit="page">1696-1697</citedRange></bibl>.</note>
